Then our son died.

484
00:25:25,828 --> 00:25:28,549
I came home from the theater one night
a couple of months later, and...

485
00:25:29,415 --> 00:25:30,874
And there's this kid who...

486
00:25:30,875 --> 00:25:33,763
Well, I don't think she ever
had a real drink in her life before.

487
00:25:36,339 --> 00:25:39,560
There she is stretched out
across the bed dead drunk

488
00:25:40,802 --> 00:25:43,189
with her wrists cut and bleeding like a...

489
00:25:48,810 --> 00:25:53,282
She was jealous of the fact that
I had my work and something to live for.

490
00:25:54,232 --> 00:25:56,577
She felt she had nothing, you see?

491
00:25:59,112 --> 00:26:02,041
Inside of a year,
she was a hopeless drunkard.

492
00:26:05,284 --> 00:26:08,589
So, in an effort to give her
some purpose in life,

493
00:26:09,455 --> 00:26:12,260
I made her feel
that I needed her in my work.

494
00:26:12,375 --> 00:26:14,804
I let her pick
all the songs I should record

495
00:26:15,044 --> 00:26:16,722
and the shows I ought to do.

496
00:26:18,297 --> 00:26:23,271
She started taking over everything,
then she became very possessive.

497
00:26:25,054 --> 00:26:29,193
And wanted to make all the decisions,
had to be with me all the time.

498
00:26:30,101 --> 00:26:31,977
Whenever I was away from her, why,

499
00:26:31,978 --> 00:26:34,282
she acted as if I'd run off
with another woman or something.

500
00:26:35,898 --> 00:26:38,411
She had fits of depression.

501
00:26:40,862 --> 00:26:43,499
One time, she set fire to a hotel suite.

502
00:26:46,617 --> 00:26:48,754
That's when I began
hitting the bottle pretty hard.

503
00:26:52,498 --> 00:26:54,135
Does she still drink?

504
00:26:55,334 --> 00:26:56,554
No.

505
00:26:57,211 --> 00:26:58,973
She stopped when I began.

506
00:27:00,965 --> 00:27:02,393
That figures.

507
00:27:03,468 --> 00:27:06,814
You were the weak one now.
That's what she wanted.

508
00:27:10,391 --> 00:27:13,226
I suppose you have
to bring her up to Boston, huh?

509
00:27:13,227 --> 00:27:15,781
I couldn't leave her alone, Bernie.

510
00:27:15,938 --> 00:27:17,522
I guess you thought it was kind of funny

511
00:27:17,523 --> 00:27:20,453
I didn't hang around the theater
after the audition the other day.

512
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:24,237
But, gee, if I'd have taken
this part without talking to her first,

513
00:27:24,238 --> 00:27:26,250
I don't know what would have happened.

514
00:27:26,407 --> 00:27:28,617
I had to make believe
that I didn't want it,

515
00:27:28,618 --> 00:27:30,327
that I was afraid of it, you see?

516
00:27:30,328 --> 00:27:32,370
And then that left it open
for her to convince me,

517
00:27:32,371 --> 00:27:34,884
like it was her idea and not mine.

518
00:27:37,627 --> 00:27:40,514
They can get awful bent
out of shape sometimes, can't they?

519
00:27:41,506 --> 00:27:43,935
You know, my wife was so twisted,

520
00:27:44,425 --> 00:27:48,105
she once said to me,
"I hope your next play's a flop,

521
00:27:48,679 --> 00:27:51,431
so the whole world can see
how much I love you,

522
00:27:51,432 --> 00:27:53,569
even though you're a failure."

523
00:28:04,946 --> 00:28:06,374
Georgie?

524
00:28:08,241 --> 00:28:09,866
Just coming from a movie.

525
00:28:09,867 --> 00:28:12,577
Passing by, I thought
you might be through.

526
00:28:12,578 --> 00:28:14,632
Your timing was perfect, Mrs. Elgin.

527
00:28:15,039 --> 00:28:16,801
I have a knack that way.

528
00:28:16,958 --> 00:28:20,596
Good evening, Mr. Dodd.
How is my husband doing?

529
00:28:21,629 --> 00:28:25,393
Well, in my less-than-humble opinion,
he's what you call a natural.

530
00:28:26,008 --> 00:28:29,427
Don't let him kid you, honey.
I was floundering all over the place.

531
00:28:29,428 --> 00:28:32,013
We're going to have to
rehearse those cues a lot.

532
00:28:32,014 --> 00:28:35,194
You can thank her, you know, for the
six or seven words that I did know.

533
00:28:35,476 --> 00:28:36,821
Thanks.

534
00:28:38,271 --> 00:28:41,492
- Did I intrude?
- No, no. We were just breaking up.

535
00:28:42,358 --> 00:28:45,026
I don't like to make myself obtrusive
when Frank's working,

536
00:28:45,027 --> 00:28:47,623
unless, of course, he needs my help.

537
00:28:48,364 --> 00:28:53,170
- You're sure I'm not in the way?
