567
00:31:05,710 --> 00:31:08,712
If I tell him he's magnificent,
he says I'm not being honest.

568
00:31:08,713 --> 00:31:11,256
If I tell him he's not magnificent,
he says I don't love him.

569
00:31:11,257 --> 00:31:13,300
Why don't you tell him he's good
but can be better?

570
00:31:13,301 --> 00:31:16,594
- Is that what the critics will tell him?
- Are you a critic or a wife?

571
00:31:16,595 --> 00:31:19,775
Let's say I try in my small way to help.

572
00:31:21,934 --> 00:31:24,936
That's what my ex-wife
used to keep reminding me of.

573
00:31:24,937 --> 00:31:26,354
Tearfully.

574
00:31:26,355 --> 00:31:29,994
She had a theory that behind every
great man there was a great woman.

575
00:31:30,359 --> 00:31:33,445
She also was thoroughly convinced
that she was great

576
00:31:33,446 --> 00:31:37,293
and that all I needed to qualify
was guidance on her part.

577
00:31:37,783 --> 00:31:39,753
She worked hard at it.

578
00:31:40,036 --> 00:31:41,411
Too hard.

